In this paper we show that
parallel to\f((PUP1-lambda)-U-lambda)\parallel to less than or equal to max {parallel to\f (T)\parallel to, parallel to\U* . f(T) . U + f (0)(I - U*U)parallel to\}
where T is an element of B(H), parallel to\ . parallel to\ is a semi-norm on B(H) which satisfies some conditions, T = UP (polar decomposition), 0 less than or equal to X less than or equal to I and f is a polynomial. As a consequence of this fact, we will show that some semi-norms \parallel to . parallel to\ including the p-radii (0 &lt; rho less than or equal to 2) satisfy the inequality \parallel tof((PUP1-lambda)-U-lambda)parallel to\ less than or equal to parallel to\f(T)\parallel to. We also give some related results. (C) 2003 Published by Elsevier Inc.
